1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,746
{\an8}<i>Knowing the Moravianos,</i>
<i>they won't move without directions.</i>

2
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,414
{\an8}<i>Clearly, they have a target.</i>

3
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:41,708
{\an8}Which is my close friend?

4
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:44,711
{\an8}And when they target you,
they target to kill you.

5
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:46,254
{\an8}Yes. Only by doing so
can we get Chiara back to focus.

6
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:47,922
{\an8}<i>Back to us, where she belongs.</i>
<i>So it's time to kill this Mikoy!</i>

7
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:54,554
{\an8}<i>And Mikoy and I are allowed</i>
<i>to live a normal life that I dream of.</i>

8
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:59,726
{\an8}I just feel like I still don't know
that much about you,

9
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:01,478
{\an8}about your life.

10
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:03,897
{\an8}<i>I still don't know Chiara</i>
<i>outside her family.</i>

11
00:01:06,274 --> 00:01:09,986
{\an8}Look at the height.
It's exactly the same height as Chiara.

12
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:18,745
{\an8}That's the average height
of Filipinas, okay?

13
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:22,999
{\an8}Not all Filipinas are like you
with your model height.

14
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:24,751
{\an8}Here.

15
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:30,215
{\an8}When she wiped something off her face,

16
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:32,091
{\an8}she used her left arm.

17
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:39,974
{\an8}Remember the dart game?

18
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:53,780
{\an8}Yes.

19
00:01:53,863 --> 00:01:57,867
{\an8}But being left-handed
isn't exactly rare for a Filipina,

20
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,911
{\an8}if that even is a Filipina
you're talking about.

21
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,789
{\an8}But that's blonde hair. Look closely!

22
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:08,670
{\an8}Everything you're telling me
are just pieces of evidence

23
00:02:08,753 --> 00:02:11,881
{\an8}that might be circumstantial. Okay?

24
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:15,260
{\an8}Maybe she dyed her hair blonde
because she got bored with her life.

25
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:18,429
{\an8}Or maybe she wore a hoodie
because her hairfall got worse.

26
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,265
{\an8}Bok.

27
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:23,601
{\an8}You know how valuable
Chiara is to our asset,

28
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:26,187
{\an8}and you're risking alienating her

29
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:28,773
{\an8}from our most important asset.

30
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:30,567
{\an8}For what exactly?

31
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:35,446
{\an8}Is this really how we work as agents now?

32
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:40,577
{\an8}Well, if you're looking for my friends,

33
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:42,662
{\an8}they're in Prague.

34
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:45,290
{\an8}Didn't I tell you I grew up there?

35
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:48,418
{\an8}And even if you do meet them,
I don't think you'll like them

36
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:50,712
because they're not
as warm as your friends.

37
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:53,298
Oh, right.

38
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:56,134
You said that before.

39
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:04,267
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

40
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:06,394
Am I being too intrusive?

41
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,397
It's just that you
already know me so well,

42
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,607
from head to toe.

43
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,859
You even know every little detail.

44
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:17,697
You've even met my friends
from Cebu and Manila.

45
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,658
I just thought, you know,

46
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:23,077
I'd get to know you better

47
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:25,622
if I spent time with the people
you spend time with

48
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,582
outside your responsibilities

49
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:29,918
of being a Valtrovi.

50
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:31,961
That's all it was.

51
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:40,595
I understand why you thought that.

52
00:03:40,678 --> 00:03:44,015
But me, I'm not worried.

53
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:48,937
Because I know we still have a lot of time
to get to know each other.

54
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:57,654
Hunches are also important
in our line of work.

55
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:03,618
I know, but we need concrete evid--

56
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:15,338
I heard you mentioning
something about a hunch.

57
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,135
I have a question for you.

58
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:23,763
Which came first?

59
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:26,516
The egg or the chicken?

60
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:29,978
That's what you were arguing about?

61
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:34,983
Because what we were really talking about
was our lunch later, right?

62
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:36,234
Not hunch.

63
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:38,820
Anyway, sir.

64
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:41,197
The egg or the chicken?

65
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,409
Even if we leave this world,

66
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,828
no one will ever answer that question.

67
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:50,123
So instead of sulking there,

68
00:04:50,206 --> 00:04:52,208
come with me to the conference room.

69
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:57,505
In uniform, check!

70
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:00,049
Giving orders, check!

71
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,467
Grumpy, check!

72
00:05:08,224 --> 00:05:11,394
So, come to the conference room.

73
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,605
I'll tell you what happened. Come on.

74
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:17,692
You? The egg or the chicken?

75
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:19,569
I don't get you. Hurry up already.

76
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:21,779
You're as pale as an egg.

77
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,245
Angelito.

78
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:33,833
Yes, you're taking forever.

79
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,251
I've been here for a while.

80
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,628
You didn't even say
you'd wait for me here.

81
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:39,047
What if I didn't come straight here?

82
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,798
- Then your eyes would've turned white.
- Stop getting annoyed already.

83
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,091
Give me that.

84
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,427
It looks like you're having a hard time,
that's why you're so grumpy.

85
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:50,266
Why, what is that?

86
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,935
You don't have a fever.

87
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:54,479
Why are you like that?

88
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,025
I'm perfectly fine.

89
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:01,110
My immune system is really strong.

90
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,320
Why?

91
00:06:02,403 --> 00:06:03,780
Am I not allowed to be nice to you?

92
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:07,450
If someone's nice to you,
they're automatically sick?

93
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:09,202
I'm just looking out for you

94
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:13,247
because you're like that with me too.

95
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:16,084
You kind of take care of me

96
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:18,836
in your own weird way.

97
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:20,797
Right?

98
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:25,968
What if we go to the mall
after your class?

99
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:30,723
Yes, if that's okay with you.

100
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:35,686
Why did you suddenly decide to invite me?

101
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:36,813
What's that?

102
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:38,815
Is something wrong with your mouth?
Maybe a mouth sore?

103
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,069
Nothing really.

104
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:46,447
So you can have fun

105
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:50,076
and forget about
your stressors for a while.

106
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:52,036
I'm not used to seeing you like that.

107
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:53,996
Punching people.

108
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,374
You're still not over that.

109
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:57,959
But…

110
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:02,839
Since you're being so sweet right now,
fine, I'll go with you.

111
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:04,799
I'm game for the movie.

112
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:05,925
Okay then.

113
00:07:06,008 --> 00:07:09,011
I'll walk you to your class first,
then after your class,

114
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,513
I'll see you outside, okay?

115
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,474
- Okay.
- Alright, let's go.

116
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:22,775
Are we waiting for someone?

117
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:29,782
Okay.

118
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,617
Senator Quintin.

119
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:35,121
Traffic as usual.

120
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:36,914
Is it really traffic?

121
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:40,042
Ever since I was single, that has
already been our country's problem.

122
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:44,547
Now I'm already the Chief Director,
and it's still our problem.

123
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,591
Plus other things,

124
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:51,179
like drugs, syndicates,
gambling, corruption, goodness.

125
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:54,098
If we go through
every single problem in this country,

126
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:56,058
we won't finish this meeting.

127
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:05,276
Before anything else,
this is why I'm dressed like this.

128
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:08,070
The fool, Chief Velasco,
is actually on leave,

129
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:11,532
and he invited me to play golf
at his favorite golf course

130
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:13,117
to talk about your issue.

131
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,373
Yes, the one who loves
playing golf to de-stress.

132
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:22,335
If you were the one who won the lottery,

133
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:23,836
you'd have all the time in the world.

134
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,795
But anyway,

135
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:26,714
the good news is,

136
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:31,511
you, my friend, are going to keep
your position for a very long time,

137
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:35,473
and now you can go back to stressing
over the country's problems again

138
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:38,017
because we revoked your resignation.

139
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,060
There it is!

140
00:08:40,269 --> 00:08:41,938
Keep your voice down.
This is embarrassing.

141
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:46,067
It's okay, I know you're excited
to have your father figure back.

142
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:50,488
My announcement isn't over yet.

143
00:08:50,571 --> 00:08:51,656
There's a catch.

144
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:55,076
They're sending someone
to monitor your agency closely,

145
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:58,120
and you need to coordinate
with the National Police

146
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:01,749
on every move, every breath,
every touch you make.

147
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:05,294
And the person
they sent to monitor you is him.

148
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:06,462
Come in, dear!

149
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:25,690
- You?!
- What?!

150
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:28,943
Oh my God.

151
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,289
Hold on.

152
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,124
Hold on.

153
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,091
Who are you?

154
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:06,814
Oh, gosh, Bok.

155
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:12,236
We don't need a walking CCTV around us.

156
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,447
What does the National Police
want from us anyway?

157
00:10:15,156 --> 00:10:19,952
First, they wanted to remove
an efficient employee.

158
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,996
Second, what they want

159
00:10:22,079 --> 00:10:25,207
is for us to be monitored
on every move we make.

160
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,792
Are we incompetent?

161
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:32,673
I also don't agree with what they want.

162
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:36,927
But we're already in this situation,
and the verdict is final.

163
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:39,597
You know we'll just get angry,
but nothing will happen.

164
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:42,475
Nothing will happen.

165
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:44,977
We'll just keep ranting, but nothing.

166
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,103
It'll still be the same.

167
00:10:46,687 --> 00:10:48,272
But what's really surprising

168
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,483
is it's really Ben!

169
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:54,028
Wasn't he the one who lost a witness
because of being too overconfident?

170
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:55,279
- Bok.
- Joe.

171
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,281
- Move that away. I'll sit here.
- Bok, two o'clock.

172
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:58,783
- He is approaching.
- I like this spot.

173
00:11:14,965 --> 00:11:15,800
Hey?

174
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:20,888
Just a moment ago, you were chatting.

175
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:25,393
Then I arrived, and you all went quiet.

176
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:28,813
Were you talking about me?

177
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:30,731
The file?

178
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:33,484
- Send it to me already.
- Do not flatter yourself.

179
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,445
You're not that relevant.

180
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:57,466
I'm back to being relevant
to your life again,

181
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:01,887
and this time, you can't ghost me anymore.

182
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:19,405
That's a parcel, right?

183
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:21,991
- You're a scammer.
- What?

184
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:25,244
What do you mean, what?
I already know that modus.

185
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:28,164
You come here
to the house, knock, and say,

186
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,250
Then the payment is COD?

187
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:34,211
A lot of my neighbors
already got scammed by that, okay?

188
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,089
But not me, darling,
because I don't use COD.

189
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:40,050
All my online shopping,
I pay through e-wallet.

190
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:41,802
Okay? Goodbye.

191
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,350
Look, I'm not wearing a helmet.

192
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:49,643
I don't have a motorcycle.

193
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:00,905
He sent you here?

194
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:05,451
So you're the package?

195
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:29,975
Is anything wrong, dear?

196
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:32,520
Is this about…

197
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:34,813
Mikoy?

198
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:44,698
He said he wants to get to know Chiara

199
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:47,910
outside of her family and business.

200
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:55,501
He said he wants to get to know
my friends and stuff.

201
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:57,836
Well then…

202
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:04,885
He wants to know you completely,
the other side of you.

203
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,055
Oh, right.

204
00:14:08,138 --> 00:14:13,018
That version of you
is kind of complicated,

205
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:16,939
and apparently, you're living
a double life when it comes to Mikoy.

206
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:18,190
Mom!

207
00:14:18,274 --> 00:14:19,441
But dear,

208
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:27,658
aren't you tired yet?

209
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:45,593
Isn't that right, my dear?

210
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:49,471
Why don't you just tell Mikoy the truth?

211
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:52,641
I know, I get it.

212
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,935
There's a chance he'll leave you,

213
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:57,313
but if he really loves you,

214
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,649
he'll still accept you completely,

215
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,610
flaws and all.

216
00:15:09,783 --> 00:15:13,579
I know the things you're doing
aren't exactly something to be proud of,

217
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:16,540
those security measures for this family,

218
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:20,252
but you did it out of love.

219
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:22,963
Because you love me and your father,

220
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:25,090
because you're protecting this family,

221
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:29,970
and I know Mikoy will understand that
because he's a great guy,

222
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,932
and he's such a good son.

223
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,810
I know he'd also do everything
for his parents.

224
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:39,605
Maybe your father is right.

225
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:42,274
You need to tell Mikoy the truth.

226
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:46,904
So the weight in your chest
can somehow lessen.

227
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,931
I don't think I need a secretary.

228
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:16,058
I can manage my job anyway.

229
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:17,267
I just need, you know,

230
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:20,813
a bit of rest, and I'm as good as new.

231
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:39,039
But instead of giving instructions,

232
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,457
I might as well just do it myself.

233
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,583
I can handle it.

234
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:34,303
It's just the two of us here now.

235
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,263
So be honest with me.

236
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:41,310
Why did the National Police send someone

237
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:43,812
to monitor the agency?

238
00:17:44,563 --> 00:17:47,191
Do they suspect any of my people?

239
00:17:48,692 --> 00:17:51,487
It's a safety measure, my friend.

240
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,113
No hard feelings.

241
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:55,991
They were informed
that someone wants to kill you,

242
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:56,992
and if that happens,

243
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:59,745
it will be a big blow
to the National Police.

244
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:04,208
Chief Velaso also said
that you're not alone in this fight.

245
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:24,144
Is it because of his past
with your adopted daughter?

246
00:18:25,312 --> 00:18:28,941
Agent Alex has a mind of her own.

247
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:36,448
That guy might get killed before I do.

248
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:41,203
That's the General Ruiz I know.

249
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:46,458
The so-called terror of Bataan.

250
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:50,921
No impact!

251
00:18:56,218 --> 00:19:00,472
Like "Butuan's Executioner"!

252
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:03,058
Oh, come on, you still can't move on.

253
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:07,354
Well, he did get a better title
after all, then got it--

254
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,620
I'm just glad you're safe, my friend.

255
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:59,156
<i>Skintone? It's kinda dull.</i>

256
00:19:59,656 --> 00:20:00,908
<i>How about this?</i>

257
00:20:00,991 --> 00:20:02,659
<i>It's too revealing.</i>

258
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:08,081
<i>I think this is it! Pink.</i>

259
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:11,835
<i>To look sweet! See? Perfect!</i>

260
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:25,015
PHILIPPINE UNIVERSITY

261
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:31,313
<i>Where could he be?</i>

262
00:20:35,817 --> 00:20:37,152
He's taking too long.

263
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:38,946
<i>Where are you Angelito?</i>

264
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:40,364
<i>Why aren't you answering my calls?</i>

265
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:41,990
What time is it?!

266
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:46,787
This Angelito is really annoying!

267
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:49,998
He told us to watch a movie
so I could de-stress,

268
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:53,418
and now he's the reason I'm stressed!

269
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,295
- I told you.
- Sofie?

270
00:21:01,051 --> 00:21:01,969
Wow.

271
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:04,680
Is there really no subtlety
in your reaction?

272
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:06,848
It's like your face has subtitles.

273
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:08,558
I can clearly see
you're disappointed to see me.

274
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:11,103
Ouch.

275
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:13,397
Don't you remember me?

276
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,648
I'm the one who was with Angelito before,

277
00:21:14,731 --> 00:21:16,692
when you brought Owen along to apologize.

278
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:20,445
Sorry, I don't remember you.

279
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:30,497
Okay, Laurence
with a letter U and not a W,

280
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:32,749
if you're really Angelito's friend,

281
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,626
do you know where he is?

282
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,047
But now he's a no-show.

283
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:40,841
No.

284
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:42,718
I didn't see him at the dorm either.

285
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:45,345
Actually, I was also
about to watch a movie.

286
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:47,097
Want me to join you instead?

287
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:49,975
This is so annoying!

288
00:21:50,058 --> 00:21:51,184
Wait.

289
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:59,484
Why did you assign Carlota
as Mikoy's secretary?

290
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:02,946
You didn't even ask me.

291
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:12,789
She's like the female version of Vicek,

292
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:16,001
but without a traitor's blood.

293
00:22:26,428 --> 00:22:29,931
We are the danger to Mikoy and his family.

294
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:35,520
You already know the answer.

295
00:22:39,232 --> 00:22:41,109
And if you want Mikoy out,

296
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,779
you also know what needs to be done.

297
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:50,911
The truth is finally out.

298
00:22:53,663 --> 00:22:57,751
You're only doing this
because you're still suspicious of Mikoy.

299
00:22:57,834 --> 00:23:02,130
That's why you took Carlota
to investigate him, right?

300
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:53,181
Alright then.

301
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:54,599
Do a cartwheel into a split.

302
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,685
Sure, sir! That's my favorite!

303
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,270
Wait.

304
00:24:00,647 --> 00:24:01,898
Here I come.

305
00:24:16,663 --> 00:24:19,958
Sir, if you didn't know,
I used to be a gymnast.

306
00:24:20,041 --> 00:24:22,669
I was part of the national team.

307
00:24:22,752 --> 00:24:24,629
Do you want another one, sir?

308
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,381
Or anything else you want me to do?

309
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:28,300
No, it's okay.

310
00:24:33,096 --> 00:24:35,348
Go ahead, cross the misua.

311
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:38,560
- Let's see how good you are.
- Misua!

312
00:24:52,449 --> 00:24:53,700
Apologies, sir,

313
00:24:53,783 --> 00:24:56,203
but I promise I'll find out what misua is.

314
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:00,373
Once I learn what misua is,

315
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:02,375
I promise I'll cross it.

316
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:04,920
I'll study it. Sorry, sir.

317
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,010
No, I'm good.

318
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:13,303
It's okay.

319
00:25:18,099 --> 00:25:20,352
I'll just take care of something.

320
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:03,561
Hello, Alex, we have a problem.

321
00:26:05,355 --> 00:26:06,564
Something like that.

322
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:09,985
Where are you now?

323
00:26:11,861 --> 00:26:14,364
There were changes in my position
as COO of Vertex.

324
00:26:14,447 --> 00:26:17,158
Wait, what changes? Did you get fired?

325
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:18,159
No.

326
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:24,582
That's a big problem.
Did Chiara want this?

327
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:26,334
No.

328
00:26:26,418 --> 00:26:27,627
I actually don't know.

329
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:29,421
We haven't talked about it yet,

330
00:26:29,504 --> 00:26:31,214
but her father ordered it.

331
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:33,466
But for sure, she won't like this.

332
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:35,552
How are you so sure?

333
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:39,681
I just feel it.

334
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:41,224
That's just how Chiara is.

335
00:26:41,808 --> 00:26:44,436
<i>You know, whenever girls get close to me,</i>

336
00:26:44,519 --> 00:26:45,812
<i>she gets mad.</i>

337
00:26:45,895 --> 00:26:48,440
She's a bit of a jealous type.

338
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:49,899
<i>Mikoy, I just want to know.</i>

339
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:52,944
How well do you really know Chiara?

340
00:27:24,351 --> 00:27:26,061
It looks like someone
is investigating her.

